        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Exeter&#44; New  Hampshire&#44;<lb/>
                February 18&#44; 1884.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais&#44;<lb/>
                My dear sir&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>I am respectfully referred to you<lb/> as a learned Israelite for information<lb/> upon a subject or two&#44; to which I have<lb/> been giving some study&#44; thus far with&#45;<lb/>out satisfactory results.<lb/></p>
            <p>I have an impression that the Jews<lb/> believe that the true Christ &#91;or <hi rend="underline">Messiah</hi>&#44;<lb/> as I think they prefer to name Christ<lb/> &#40;Why&#63;&#41;&#93;&#91;previous brackets used by author&#93; is yet to come. If so&#44; why do<lb/> they believe this. Why do they make Sat&#45;<lb/>urday their Sabbath day&#63; Have you a creed<lb/> or articles of faith&#63; Any information you<lb/> may be pleased to write to me concerning the Jews<lb/> will be thankfully received. Can you name to<lb/> me some book&#44; and the publisher of the<lb/> same&#44; that will give me&#44; in addition to what<lb/> you may kindly write&#44; further information&#63;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Of what does your Bible consist&#63; The Old<lb/> Testament only&#63; If so&#44; why do you reject<lb/> the New Testament&#63; Can you not give a<lb/> reason for the faith that is within you&#63;<lb/></p> 
            <p>The poet Milton&#44; in his &#34;Paradise Regained&#44;&#34;<lb/> Book I&#44; lines  242&#45;245&#44; wrote&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>&#34;At thy nativity&#44; a glorious choir<lb/>
                Of <hi rend="underline">angels</hi>&#44; in the fields of Bethlehem&#44; sing<lb/>
                To shepherds&#44; watching at their folds by night&#44;<lb/>
                And told them the <hi rend="underline">Messiah</hi> now was born.&#34;<lb/></p> 
            <p>Why did Milton use the name Messiah&#44; <lb/> and not Christ&#63; Although&#44; at the age of 21 years&#44;<lb/> he wrote a sublime hymn&#44; with the title&#45;&#45;<lb/> &#34;On  the Morning of <hi rend="underline">Christ&#39;s</hi> Nativity.&#34;<lb/></p>
            <p>What do you understand by an <hi rend="underline">angel</hi>&#63;<lb/> Webster&#44; in his Unabridged Dictionary&#44; <lb/> defines an <hi rend="underline">angel</hi>&#45;&#45;&#34;a <hi rend="underline">spirit</hi>&#44; or a <hi rend="underline">spiritual</hi><lb/> being&#44; employed by God to communicate<lb/> his will to man.&#34;  When a boy&#44; in the<lb/> Sabbath school&#44; I was taught to sing&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>&#34; I want to be an <hi rend="underline">angel</hi>&#44;<lb/>
                And with the <hi rend="underline">angels</hi> stand&#59;<lb/>
                A crown upon my forehead&#44;<lb/>
                A harp within my hand.&#34;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Artists&#44; in painting pictures of <hi rend="underline">angels</hi>&#44; repre&#45;<lb/>sent them as <hi rend="underline">human</hi> beings with wings.<lb/> I never heard of any in these later days.<lb/></p>
            <p>Can you give me any information re&#45;<lb/>garding the words or ideas&#8212;<hi rend="underline">omnipotent</hi>&#44;<lb/> <hi rend="underline">omniscient</hi> and <hi rend="underline">omnipresent</hi>&#8212;Divine attributes&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>&#34;But to do good and to communicate<lb/> forget not&#58; for with such sacrifices God<lb/> is well pleased.&#34;<lb/></p>
            <p>I shall be most happy and very grate&#45;<lb/>ful to you&#44; if you will kindly write to<lb/> me information&#44; which you are doubtless<lb/> well able to give&#44; upon the several sub&#45;<lb/>jects&#44; of which I have herein written.<lb/></p>
            <p>At any time&#44; when I can serve you&#44;<lb/> feel free to command me.<lb/>
                Fraternally yours&#45;&#45;<lb/>
                Charles Marseilles&#44;<lb/>
                &#40;Journalist.&#41;<lb/></p>
        </body>
